    <section anchor="FastFedMetadata" title="FastFed Metadata">
      <t>
	This specification extends the <xref target="FastFed.Core">FastFed
        Core</xref> metadata (Section 3.3.1) with the following value
        for <spanx style="verb">sso_protocols_supported</spanx>:
	<list style="hanging">
	  <t hangText="OIDC">
            A Provider who includes the value <spanx style="verb">OIDC</spanx> in
            the  <spanx style="verb">sso_protocols_supported</spanx> indicates
            they comply with the requirements described in this specification.
	  </t>
	</list>
      </t>
      <t>
        The following is a non-normative example of Provider Metadata showing
        the usage of the value:
      </t>
        <figure><artwork><![CDATA[
 {
   "identity_provider": {
     "capabilities": {
       "sso_protocols_supported": ["OIDC"],
   ...
 }
]]></artwork></figure> 
    </section>
    
    <section anchor="FastFedHandshake" title="FastFed Handshake">

      <t>
	When using the OpenID Connect protocol, the FastFed
        Identity Provider and Application Provider have various
        responsibilities to comply with the protocol.
      </t>
      <t>
        The Identity Provider fulfills the role of an OpenID Provider. It has
        a responsibility to support OpenID Connect Discovery and Dynamic
        Client Registration as described in
        <xref target="OIDCInteroperabilityIdentityProviderReqs"/>.
      </t>
      <t>
        The Application Provider fulfills the role of an OpenID Relying
        Party. It has a responsibility to perform Dynamic Registration with the
        provider, as described in
        <xref target="OIDCInteroperabilityApplicationProviderReqs"/>
      </t>
      <t>
        This specification extends the <xref target="FastFed.Core">FastFed
        Core</xref> handshake messages with additional attributes necessary for
        each party to fulfill their respective obligations under OpenID Connect.
      </t>

      <section anchor="FastFedHandshakeRegistrationRequest" title="FastFed Registration Request">
	<t>
	  This specification extends the JWT contents of the FastFed
	  Registration Request (Section 6.2.3.1
	  of <xref target="FastFed.Core">FastFord Core</xref>) with the following
	  attributes:
          <list style="hanging">
            <t hangText="oidc_configuration_uri">
	      Specifies the Issuer <spanx style="verb">location</spanx> for
	      OpenID Provider Configuration Information, as defined in
	      Section 4 of <xref target="OpenID.Discovery">OpenID Connect
	      Discovery 1.0</xref>.
            </t>
	    <t hangText="oidc_initial_access_token">
	      Specifies the <spanx style="verb">Initial Access Token</spanx>
	      for a Client Registration Endpoint, as defined in Section 3 of
	      <xref target="OpenID.Registration">OpenID Connect Dynamic
		Client Registration 1.0</xref>.
            </t>
          </list>
	</t>
	<t>
          The following is a non-normative example of the contents of a
          registration request message prior to serialization:
	</t>
        <figure><artwork><![CDATA[
 {
  "iss": "https://idp.example.com",
  "sub": "tenant-12345",
  "aud": "https://app.example.com",
  "sso_protocol": "OIDC",
  "user_schema": "urn:ietf:params:scim:schemas:core:2.0:User",
  "user_provisioning_mode": "JIT",
  "state": "liK9x2fUOWoi1P0",
  "oidc_configuration_uri=": "https://tenant-12345.idp.example.com/.well-known/openid-configuration",
  "oidc_initial_access_token": "dXNFAMwfF9pCQZI"
 }
]]></artwork></figure>
      </section>

    </section> <!-- End of FastFed Handshake Extensions -->

    <section anchor="SchemaBinding" title="Schema Binding">

      <t>
	FastFed recommmends SCIM for user schemas.
      </t>
      <t>
	This specification defines how to be FastFed Compliant when using SCIM
	schemas and endpoints with the OpenID Connect protocol.
      </t>

      <section anchor="SchemaBindingScimToOidcClaimMapping"
	       title="SCIM-to-OIDC Claim Mapping">

	<t>
	  OpenID Relying Parties MAY request the OpenID Connect Standard
	  Claims as defined in Section 5.1 of <xref target="OpenID.Core">OpenID
	  Connect Core 1.0</xref>.
	</t>
	<t>
	  OpenID Providers MUST return values for the requested claims if a
	  reasonable translation exists between the SCIM attribute and the
	  OpenID Claim. OpenID Providers SHOULD use the following translation
	  table for this purpose.
	</t>
	<t>
	  Note: SCIM attributes below refer to the "User" Resource
	  Schema defined in Section 4.1 of the <xref target="RFC7643">SCIM Core
	  Specification</xref>. Individual members of a JSON structure are
	  referenced in the table using the JSON path syntax defined in Section
	  3.5.2 of the <xref target="RFC7644">SCIM Protocol</xref>.
	</t>
	<texttable>
	  <ttcol>OpenID Claim</ttcol>
	  <ttcol>SCIM Attribute</ttcol>
	  
	  <c>sub</c>
	  <c>id</c>
	  
          <c>name</c>
          <c>name.formatted</c>
	  
          <c>given_name</c>
          <c>name.givenName</c>
	  
          <c>family_name</c>
          <c>name.familyName</c>
	  
          <c>middle_name</c>
          <c>name.middleName</c>
	  
          <c>nickname</c>
          <c>nickName</c>
	  
          <c>preferred_username</c>
          <c>userName</c>
	  
          <c>profile</c>
          <c>profileUrl</c>
	  
	  <c>picture</c>
          <c>photos[type eq "photo"].value</c>
	  
          <c>email</c>
          <c>emails[primary eq true].value</c>
	  
          <c>zoneinfo</c>
          <c>timezone</c>
	  
          <c>locale</c>
          <c>locale</c>
	  
          <c>phone_number</c>
          <c>phoneNumbers[primary eq true].value</c>
	  
          <c>address.formatted</c>
          <c>addresses[primary eq true].formatted</c>
	  
          <c>address.street_address</c>
          <c>addresses[primary eq true].streetAddress</c>
	  
          <c>address.locality</c>
          <c>addresses[primary eq true].locality</c>
	  
          <c>address.region</c>
          <c>addresses[primary eq true].region</c>
	  
          <c>address.postal_code</c>
          <c>addresses[primary eq true].postalCode</c>
	  
          <c>address.country</c>
          <c>addresses[primary eq true].country</c>
	</texttable>
